{"title":"Kogel chisels out Kolossos oversized MTB derailleur cage for SRAM Eagle","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/02/17/kogel-chisels-out-kolossos-oversized-mtb-derailleur-cage-for-sram-eagle/","date":1613586728000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>For those looking for every performance gain possible, Kogel is at it again. This time, their Kolossos oversized derailleur cage family has expanded into the world of MTB. Specifically, for the likes of SRAM Eagle rear derailleurs.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Kogel-Kolossus-Eagle-derailleur-cage-oversized-pulley-mtb-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Kogel-Kolossus-Eagle-derailleur-cage-oversized-pulley-mtb-1.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x323/rscb8/ng:webp/ngcb8\" alt=\"Kolossos oversized MTB derailleur cage for SRAM Eagle bottom\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Kogel-Kolossus-Eagle-derailleur-cage-oversized-pulley-mtb-1.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x323/rscb8/ng:webp/ngcb8\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Kogel-Kolossus-Eagle-derailleur-cage-oversized-pulley-mtb-1.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Kogel-Kolossus-Eagle-derailleur-cage-oversized-pulley-mtb-1-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Kogel-Kolossus-Eagle-derailleur-cage-oversized-pulley-mtb-1-800x533.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Kogel-Kolossus-Eagle-derailleur-cage-oversized-pulley-mtb-1-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Kogel-Kolossus-Eagle-derailleur-cage-oversized-pulley-mtb-1-768x512.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Kogel-Kolossus-Eagle-derailleur-cage-oversized-pulley-mtb-1-696x464.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Kogel-Kolossus-Eagle-derailleur-cage-oversized-pulley-mtb-1-1068x712.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Kogel-Kolossus-Eagle-derailleur-cage-oversized-pulley-mtb-1-630x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 630w\" ezoid=\"0.1520044705626551\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Kogel-Kolossus-Eagle-derailleur-cage-oversized-pulley-mtb-1.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Kogel-Kolossus-Eagle-derailleur-cage-oversized-pulley-mtb-1-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Kogel-Kolossus-Eagle-derailleur-cage-oversized-pulley-mtb-1-800x533.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Kogel-Kolossus-Eagle-derailleur-cage-oversized-pulley-mtb-1-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Kogel-Kolossus-Eagle-derailleur-cage-oversized-pulley-mtb-1-768x512.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Kogel-Kolossus-Eagle-derailleur-cage-oversized-pulley-mtb-1-696x464.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Kogel-Kolossus-Eagle-derailleur-cage-oversized-pulley-mtb-1-1068x712.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Kogel-Kolossus-Eagle-derailleur-cage-oversized-pulley-mtb-1-630x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 630w\"></a></p><p>You may recall that when <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/01/02/kogel-kolossos-oversized-derailleur-pulley-cage-offers-colossal-stiffness-low-friction/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Kogel introduced the Kolossus system</a> for road and gravel bikes, at the time, they claimed it was the stiffest cage on the market in terms of road and gravel rear derailleurs. Even so, that wasn’t stiff enough to qualify as a mountain bike derailleur cage, so the Kolossos SRAM Eagle has put on some bulk with a heavily reinforced cage design. In spite of the larger 19 tooth bottom pulley and 14 tooth top pulley, the Kolossos Eagle is within 2mm of the stock Eagle cage, and Kogel claims that it’s nearly the same weight.</p><p><span><iframe width=\"696\" height=\"392\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ZkQXv9tTRGc?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\"></iframe></span></p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Kogel-Kolossus-Eagle-derailleur-cage-oversized-pulley-mtb-8.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Kogel-Kolossus-Eagle-derailleur-cage-oversized-pulley-mtb-8.jpg\" alt=\"Kolossos oversized MTB derailleur cage for SRAM Eagle side \" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt